      <dsc><c level="series">
            <did><unittitle>Series I: Correspondence, <unitdate type="inclusive">1938-1981</unitdate>
                    </unittitle>
            </did>
            <scopecontent><p>Most of the letters in Series I are from David Berkowitz, the Son of Sam serial
                  killer. Written while incarcerated in Attica, Berkowitz corresponded regularly
                  with Abrahamsen over a two year period. Much of the subject matter consists of
                  Berkowitz trying to self-analyze about why he committed crimes. Abrahamsen
                  continuously asked questions about Berkowitz's family, his upbringing, and his
                  relationships with other people. There are a few letters from Jessamyn West, a
                  distant relative of Nixon who assisted Abrahamsen while he was working on his book
                     <title render="italic">Nixon vs. Nixon.</title>
                    </p>
            </scopecontent>
